title: When will Russia release Michael Calvey?
description: Michael Calvey, an American investor who had been working in Russia for decades, was arrested in February 2019 and charged with fraud (Bloomberg). He is awaiting a trial that is scheduled to start in mid-April (Financial Times, intellinews, Moscow Times). Release with restrictions (e.g. house arrest, bail) will not count.

title: Before 30 July 2019, will the Russian Duma approve the "sovereign Internet" bill (Bill No. 608767-7)?
description: In 2018, legislators introduced in the Russian Duma Bill No. 608767-7, being called by some the "sovereign Internet" bill (Duma [in Russian]). This legislation would increase state authority to control the Internet in the country and has drawn protests (Polygraph, CodaStory, The Moscow Times, NPR , Bloomberg). The bill passed first reading in February 2019; if the majority of parliamentarians vote in favor of the draft law in the third reading, it is considered approved (Duma news 1 [in Russian], rferl, Duma news 2, Duma bill process).

title: Before 1 May 2019, will Mexico's Senate approve President LÃ³pez Obrador's constitutional reform proposal on a presidential recall referendum?
description: Mexico's Chamber of Deputies (lower house) passed the reform in mid-March 2019, making it one step closer to becoming law. The reform allows for a mid-term presidential recall referendum (Reuters, The Hill, Mexico News Daily, Senate Votes, Legislative Process).

title: Will the Government of Canada issue a travel advisory of "Exercise a high degree of caution," "Avoid non-essential travel," or "Avoid all travel" for New Zealand between 4 April 2019 and 12 June 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using the Canadian government's Travel health notices for the country of interest. This question will resolve as "yes" if there is a qualifying travel health notice where the 'Last updated' date is in the period of interest.

title: Will there be a biological attack resulting in multiple human casualties between 4 April 2019 and 27 November 2019?
description: A biological attack is defined as the intentional release of a pathogen (disease-causing agent) or biotoxin (poisonous substance produced by a living organism) by a government, military, paramilitary, terrorist, or criminal entity that results in unwanted harm/damage to a human, plant, or animal. A "yes" resolution requires that the media reports that the event is consistent with an intentional act and that multiple humans (excluding alleged perpetrators) are sickened, injured or killed in conjunction with the attack.

This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: Will Venezuela execute or be targeted in a national military attack between 3 April 2019 and 17 April 2019?
description: A "national military attack" includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country's national military forces (to include special forces) on another country's military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A "cyber" attack will not qualify as a "national military attack."

title: Will France's President Emmanuel Macron experience a significant leadership disruption between 3 April 2019 and 29 November 2019?
description:
A "significant leadership disruption" includes confirmed reports that the leader has:
- resigned (including the issuance of a resignation that will take effect at a later date),
- lost a confidence vote,
- formally left office,
- died,
- been forcibly removed from office for 10 or more consecutive days,
- fled or been exiled from office for 10 or more consecutive days,
- been medically incapacitated or hospitalized for 10 or more consecutive days,
- been missing (whereabouts unknown) for 10 or more consecutive days.

title: What will be the Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) Threat Index on 10 June 2019?
description: The KCNA Watch database's Threat Index is a daily measure of the number of threatening English language words published each day by the KCNA, divided by the number of English language articles published by the KCNA on that date. The Threat Index for a particular date can be found by hovering your cursor over the Threat Index chart line on the KCNA Watch homepage.

To access the data, visit https://www.top500.org/statistics/list/: - Select 'June 2019' from the 'TOP500 Release' drop down menu; - Select 'Countries' in the 'Category' drop down menu. - Click 'Submit.' Question will be resolved according to the data illustrated in the 'Countries Performance Share' pie chart.

title: Will there be a significant day-over-day increase in worldwide search interest in the term "explosion" reported by Google Trends between 4 April 2019 and 17 April 2019?
description: Google Trends tracks how often a particular search-term is entered relative to the total search-volume. Values represent search interest relative to the highest value for the given region and period of interest. A value of 100 is the peak popularity for the term during the period of interest. A value of 50 means that the term is half as popular. A score of 0 means there was not enough data for this term. This question will resolve as 'yes' if Google Trends shows a 50-point or greater increase of interest in the search term in one (1) day during the period of interest. To access the relevant data, from Google Trends:- Enter the search term of interest (as a 'Search term' not a 'Topic');- Make sure 'Worldwide' is selected for the geographic area;- Use the drop-down field to enter a 'Custom time range' corresponding to the period of interest;- Click the down arrow in the top right of the 'Interest over time' chart to download the data to a CSV file.This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.Â

title: Before 30 November 2019, will either house of India's Parliament vote on passage of a bill to repeal or amend Article 370 in India's Constitution?
description: Article 370 affords the Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir special autonomous status within the Indian union. Prior to elections commencing in April, Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his Bharatiya Janata Party made a promise to repeal Article 370 (TimesOfIndia, DailyO). The outcome of a vote is immaterial to the resolution.

title: Before 30 November 2019, will an agreement on the creation of a Middle East Strategic Alliance be signed?
description: Talks began in 2017 between Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Jordan, the United States, and Egypt about establishing the alliance (also called 'Arab NATO') (CarnegieEndowment). In April 2019, Egypt reportedly withdrew from discussions (Reuters). Variations of the name of the alliance will not affect resolution, and requirements for subsequent ratification are immaterial to the question.
option_1: Yes, with Egypt as a signatory
option_2: Yes, without Egypt as a signatory

title: Will ACLED record any civilian fatalities in Iran between 14 June 2019 and 14 July 2019?
Will the Aviation Safety Network record a hijacking or criminal occurrence between 21 May 2019 and 21 June 2019?
description: The Aviation Safety Network (ASN) covers accidents and safety issues regarding airliners, military transport planes and corporate jets. The ASN Safety Database contains detailed descriptions of over 20,300 incidents, hijackings and accidents. To access the relevant data: - Go to the ASN Safety Database; - Click on the year of interest. This question will resolve as "yes" if there is an incident with a 'H#' (Hijacking) or 'C#' (Criminal) under the 'cat' (category) column during the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: How many deaths perpetrated by Boko Haram will the Council on Foreign Relations report between 25 August 2019 and 25 November 2019?
description: The Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) Nigeria Security Tracker reports on countrywide violence stemming from political, economic and social grievances. This question will be resolved using data reported by the CFR. Â To access the relevant data, open the CFR dataset and refer to the sheet entitled 'NST Main Dataset.' The count of deaths for the period of interest is obtained by summing the 'Total Deaths' column for events in which Boko Haram is identified as a perpetrator (in the 'Boko Haram (P)' column) and 'Date' falls in the period of interest. If the count crosses the highest answer bin threshold before the close date, the question will be closed retroactively with the crossing date as the end date of the question. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.Â

title: What will be the status of the "Instability in Egypt" conflict on 26 November 2019 according to the Council on Foreign Relations' Global Conflict Tracker?
description: The Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) (https://www.cfr.org/) monitors issues and conflicts around the world. The CFR's Center for Preventive Action (CPA)'s Global Conflict Tracker (https://www.cfr.org/interactives/global-conflict-tracker#!/global-conflict-tracker) provides an overview of conflicts occurring throughout the world. This question will be resolved according to the status of the indicated conflict as listed under the 'Conflict Status' section.

title: What will be the closing value of the Brazilian Real (BRL) to one U.S. Dollar exchange rate on 18 July 2019?
How many major hurricanes (Category 3 or above) will the Eastern Pacific Ocean experience between 24 May 2019 and 24 June 2019?
Will the UK's Prime Minister Theresa May experience a significant leadership disruption between 9 May 2019 and 15 October 2019?
description:
A "significant leadership disruption" includes confirmed reports that the leader has: 
- resigned (including the issuance of a resignation that will take effect at a later date), 
- lost a confidence vote, 
- formally left office, 
- died,
- been forcibly removed from office for 10 or more consecutive days, 
- fled or been exiled from office for 10 or more consecutive days, 
- been medically incapacitated or hospitalized for 10 or more consecutive days, 
- been missing (whereabouts unknown) for 10 or more consecutive days.

title: Will the WHO declare a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC) between 9 May 2019 and 15 July 2019?
description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the World Health Organization (WHO) declares a PHEIC during the period of interest: WHO Statements.

title: What will be the average percentage cost of remitting $200 USD from Japan to China in Second Quarter 2019?
How many terrorist incidents with 15 or more dead (victims + perpetrators) will occur between 1 June 2019 and 30 June 2019 as reported by Wikipedia?
description: This question will be resolved using the number of terrorist incidents reported on Wikipedia's List of terrorist incidents page in which 15 or more deaths, both victims and perpetrators, are reported to have occurred during the period of interest. If deaths are reported as a range for an incident, the lower bound will be used to determine if the event qualifies as 15 or more. This question will be resolved based on the data reported in Wikipedia at 11:59 PM ET on the day after the close date. If the count crosses the highest answer bin threshold before the close date, the question will be closed retroactively with the crossing date as the end date of the question.
clarification: This question will be resolved using the "List of terrorist incidents in June 2019" list accessible from the Wikipedia page: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_terrorist_incidents.  Other lists available from this page will not be consulted.

title: Will there be a terrorist incident in France between 1 November 2019 and 20 November 2019 as reported by Wikipedia?
description: This question will be resolved as "yes" if a terrorist incident is reported to have occurred during the period of interest according to Wikipedia's List of terrorist incidents in France page, based on the data reported at 11:59 PM ET on the day after the close date. If a qualifying event is recorded, the question will be closed retroactively with the date of the first event as the end date of the question.

title: What will be the last value of the EURO STOXX 50 Volatility Index VSTOXX (V2TX) on 31 July 2019?
Who will win India's Chandigarh Lok Sabha election?
description: The Chandigarh Lok Sabha election is scheduled for 19 May 2019.

title: Between 9 May 2019 and 29 November 2019, will a change in the membership of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) be officially announced?
description: The six-member Gulf Cooperation Council includes Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar, Kuwait, Oman, and the United Arab Emirates (GCC1, GCC2). Amidst the Arab Spring, the GCC extended an invitation to Jordan and Morocco but neither became a member (AlJazzera). Meanwhile, Oman once threatened withdrawal (ArabianBusiness), and the ongoing crisis since 2017 between Qatar and other Council members leave some analysts wondering about the longevity of the Council (PetroleumEconomist, ArabNews). Only the announcement of a joining/leaving member(s) needs to occur during the questionâs open period, not the act of joining/leaving itself.
option_1: Yes, only that one or more new member states will join the GCC
option_2: Yes, only that one or more member states will leave the GCC

resolution: Yes, and it will be less than $2.5 billion
title: Between 9 May 2019 and 30 July 2019, will the IMF approve the release of a tranche of funds to Pakistan?
description: There is currently an "agreement in principle" on a bailout program between the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and Pakistan, though there are lingering issues to resolve (TheHinduBusinessLine, Reuters, Bloomberg, TheStatesman IMFPakistan).
option_1: Yes, and it will be less than $2.5 billion
option_2: Yes, and it will be $2.5 billion or more

title: Before 30 July 2019, will the government of Yemen and the Houthis agree on a concept of operations for phase 2 of redeployments under the Hodeidah Agreement?
description: In April 2019, the Government of Yemen and the Houthis agreed to phase 1 redeployments in and around the port city of Hodeidah (TheDefensePost, UN1, Reuters1, UNDocs, Reuters2, UN2).

title: Will ACLED record any riots in Vietnam between 21 June 2019 and 21 July 2019?Â
Will ACLED record any riots in Thailand between 7 June 2019 and 7 July 2019?
What will be the price of casual labor (unskilled, daily, without food) in Somalia in the Elwak market for June 2019?
description: The Famine Early Warning Systems Network (FEWS NET) provides early warning and analysis on acute food insecurity around the world. The question will be resolved using data downloaded from FEWS NET at: http://fews.net/content/staple-food-price-data-1995-present. The relevant price can be found where 'country' is the country of interest; 'market' is the market of interest; 'product' is the product of interest; 'period_date' is the date of interest; and 'value' is the price. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: What will be the daily closing price of gold on 10 July 2019 in USD?
description: This question will be resolved using the last daily London Bullion Market Association (LBMA) Gold Price USD (PM) http://www.lbma.org.uk/precious-metal-prices for the date of interest. To access the relevant data: - Select 'Table'; - Refer to the 'PM' column under 'USD.' Question will be closed on the day before the date of interest.

title: Will there be a significant day-over-day increase in worldwide search interest in the term "ISIS" reported by Google Trends between 1 November 2019 and 29 November 2019?
Which country will account for the largest performance share in computational power in the November 2019 TOP500 list of highest-performing computer systems?
description: TheÂ TOP500 list of the highest-performing computing systems is published twice per year, generally in June and November. Question will be resolved according to the data associated with the November 2019 TOP500 list. To access the data, visit Â https://www.top500.org/statistics/list/: - Select 'November 2019' from the 'TOP500 Release' drop down menu; - Select 'Countries' in the 'Category' drop down menu. Â  - Click 'Submit.' Question will be resolved according to the data illustrated in the 'Countries Performance Share' pie chart.

title: Will Sudan execute or be targeted in a national military attack between 16 May 2019 and 30 June 2019?
description: A "national military attack" includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country's national military forces (to include special forces) on another country's military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A "cyber" attack will not qualify as a "national military attack."

title: What will be the daily closing spot price of Brent crude oil (USD per barrel) on 12 June 2019, according to the U.S. EIA?
description: This question will be resolved using the daily closing spot price for wholesale Brent crude oil reported by the Energy Information Administration (https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/pet_pri_spt_s1_d.htm).Â

title: Will the PITF Worldwide Atrocities Dataset record an event perpetrated by a state actor in Brazil (BRA) that starts between 18 August 2019 and 18 September 2019?
description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the Political Instability Task ForceÂ (PITF) Worldwide Atrocities Dataset records any event with a start date (Start Day, Start Month, Start Year) in the period of interest, inclusive, for which 'Event Location: Country' is the country of interest, and 'Perpetrators: Perp State Role' is: 'State Perpetrator'; 'Transnational, State'; 'Multiple Perpetrators (State)'; or 'Multiple Perpetrators (State and Non-State)'. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.Â

title: How many Total Registered Syrian Refugees will be reported by the UNHCR on 15 July 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using data from the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR). The outcome will be determined by the reported number of Total Registered Syrian Refugees on the date of interest according to the UNHCR's Syria Regional Refugee Response website.Â  This question will be resolved by consulting the data source between 12:00 PM ET and 2:00 PM ET on the date of interest.

title: What will be the daily closing price of silver on 24 May 2019 in USD?
Will Julian Assange leave the UK between 16 May 2019 and 15 July 2019?
description: Julian Assange was arrested on 11 April 2019 in the UK (New York Times).

title: Between 16 May 2019 and 30 July 2019, for two consecutive Saturdays, will fewer than 5,000 cumulative daily protesters participate in "Yellow Vests" protests across France?
description: What began in November 2018 as protests against fuel tax hikes have grown into an ongoing series of protests across France, particularly on Saturdays (Bloomberg, France24(1)). President Macron has offered concessions over several months, but the protests continue (France24(2), WSJ).

title: Between 16 May 2019 and 30 July 2019, will the president of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) appoint a prime minister?
description: Disagreements between recently elected President Felix Tshisekedi of the DRC and former President Joseph Kabila (who remains influential as the leader of the majority party in the National Assembly) have produced a stalemate on a range of issues, including the appointment of a prime minister (Stratfor, TheEastAfrican, DW, Reuters). The president establishing a fact-finding mission, or "mission d'information" per Article 78 of the constitution, will not count (ConstitutionProjectDRC).

title: On 29 July 2019, how many total cases of polio will be reported by EndPolio in Pakistan for 2019?
description: Polio has been eradicated in almost all countries with a few exceptions, including Pakistan (EndPolio, NYT). In 2018, EndPolio reported 12 total polio cases. As of 15 May 2019, there were 15 total polio cases so far in 2019 for Pakistan. This question will be resolved by consulting the End Polio data between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM ET on 29 July 2019. Resolution will be based on the value observed at the time of source consultation.

title: By 28 May 2019, how many signatures will Petition #89118 receive regarding Germany's recognition of the Ukraine Holodomor as genocide?
description: Only a handful of countries have officially recognized the Ukraine Holodomor as an act of genocide (HolodomorOrg, MemorialHolodomorOrg). In order for German Ministers of Parliament to review the petition, it must first receive 50,000 signatures which can be tracked at (BundestagPetition89118 (in German; view the signature count on the right side of the page under "Anzahl Online-Mitzeichner" (translated: "Number of online subscribers")). This question will be resolved by consulting the BundestagPetition89118 between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM ET on 28 May 2019. Resolution will be based on the value observed at the time of source consultation.

title: Between 23 May 2019 and 30 July 2019, will the Spanish monarch appoint a President of the Government?
description: Spanish elections in April 2019 resulted in the Partido Socialista Obrero EspaÃ±ol (PSOE, or the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party) gaining the most seats in the Congress of Deputies, but not the majority required to form a government on its own (ElectionResults (in Spanish), Bloomberg, ElPais, EuropeBlog). Part IV: Government and Administration of the Spanish Constitution describes the nomination and appointment process (ConstitutionProject).
option_1: Yes, and (s)he will be a member of PSOE and lead a minority government
option_2: Yes, and (s)he will be a member of PSOE and lead a majority government
option_3: Yes, and (s)he will not be a member of PSOE

title: Between 23 May 2019 and 29 November 2019, how many formal UN-sponsored talks will be convened between Morocco and the Polisario Front to address the Western Sahara conflict?
description: Decades old, the conflict over the Western Sahara is one of Africa's longest (CarnegieCouncil). After six years of stalled talks, Morocco and the Polisario Front have reconvened negotiations twice, once in December 2018 and again in March 2019 (ReliefWeb1, UNDocsWesternSahara). In April 2019, the UN extended its mission to the region again, but only for six months, versus one year, in hopes the momentum towards progress continues (ReliefWeb2).

title: Before 30 November 2019, will Germany's Bundestag adopt a bill that would impose a fine on parents who refuse a measles vaccine for their children?
description: In the wake of the recent measles outbreak across Europe (EuroNews), German Health Minister Jens Spahn has drafted legislation imposing a fine on parents who refuse the measles vaccine for their children (TheGuardian). Adoption by the Bundestag entails passing three readings before proceeding to the next stage of the legislative process (Bundestag, GermanConstitution).

title: Before 30 July 2019, will Saad Dinar be released?
description: On 29 April 2019, Libyan Oil Workers' Union head Saad Dinar (also known as Saad Dinar el Fakhri) was reportedly captured by armed assailants (NOC, Reuters, Alwasat). For the purposes of this question, 'released' could include, but is not restricted to escape, rescue, or captor return, and he must be released alive.

title: Will the United Kingdom (UK) leave the European Union (EU) before 1 November 2019?
description: The UK is scheduled to leave EU at 7 PM ET on 31 October 2019 (11:00 PM GMT on 31 October 2019). For more information on the negotiation and conclusion of a withdrawal agreement and the revocation or extension of the Article 50 period, see (Europa1) and (Europa2).

title: Will the Government of Canada issue a travel advisory of "Avoid non-essential travel" or "Avoid all travel" for China between 23 May 2019 and 21 August 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using the Canadian government's Travel Advice and Advisories for the country of interest (https://travel.gc.ca/destinations/china). The question will resolve as "yes" if, during the period of interest, an advisory of interest is listed in the 'Risk Level(s)' tab with 'Last updated' in the period of interest. Regional advisories will count toward resolution; that is, if an advisory of interest is issued for even one region of the country of interest, the question will resolve as "yes."

title: Will there be an earthquake of magnitude 8.5 or stronger worldwide between 23 May 2019 and 31 October 2019?
What will be the daily closing price of platinum on 25 June 2019 in USD?
How much crude oil will Iraq produce in October 2019?

This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: How many battle deaths will ACLED record in India in June 2019?
Between 23 May 2019 and 29 November 2019, how many tranches will the IMF approve for release to Ukraine?
description: In December 2018, the International Monetary Fund (IMF) approved a 14-month, $3.9-billion loan program for Ukraine (IMF Press Release, Bloomberg1, IMF-Ukraine). The recent presidential elections in April 2019, the planned parliamentary elections in October 2019, and other political considerations could affect the policies necessary for the funds to be released (Bloomberg2, UNIAN, Interfax, CNBC). The amount of each tranche is irrelevant for the resolution of this question.

title: Between 30 May 2019 and 29 November 2019, will an Ebola health worker be injured or killed in an attack against an Ebola facility inside the Central African Republic, South Sudan, Uganda, Rwanda, Burundi, or Tanzania?
description: Frequent and sometimes even deadly attacks against the Ebola response efforts in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) threaten successful containment of the disease to DRC's borders (Economist, AlJazeera, Vox, France24). Some high risk countries bordering DRC, for example Uganda, have instituted preparedness responses (WHO).

title: How many of Ukraine's Central Election Commission (CEC) members will cease to be a member by 29 July 2019?
description: As of question launch, there are sixteen members of Ukraine's CEC: Tetiana SLIPACHUK, Oleh KONOPOLSKYI, Yevhenii RADCHENKO, Nataliia BERNATSKA, Alla BASALAIEVA, Mykhailo VERBENSKYI, Oleh DIDENKO, Andrii YEVSTIHNIEIEV, Iryna YEFREMOVA, Olga ZHELTOVA, Svitlana KUSTOVA, Olga LOTIUK, Kateryna MAKHNITSKA, Vitalii PLUKAR, Leontii SHYPILOV, and Tetiana YUZKOVA (in Ukrainian: UkraineGov). Ukraine's CEC was overhauled towards the end of 2018 (KyivPost) and will oversee the upcoming snap parliamentary elections (BBC, USIP). If the 17th CEC position (vacant at time of question launch) is filled during the question period, and that individual subsequently ceases to be a member, it will count towards resolution.

title: Will Iran close the Strait of Hormuz for any length of time between 30 May 2019 and 20 July 2019?
description: In April 2019, Iran announced that they were prepared to block the Strait of Hormuz amid escalating geopolitical tensions (Bloomberg). Announcements of intent to close the Strait of Hormuz are not sufficient to resolve this question.

title: How many strikes and worker protests will China Labour Bulletin record as having occurred between 28 July 2019 and 28 August 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using the data associated with China Labour Bulletin's (CLB) Strike Map (https://maps.clb.org.hk/strikes/en#). All events reported by CLB are considered strikes or worker protests, so the answer will be a simple count of all records (rows) in the Strike Map data with dates that fall in the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

If deaths are reported as a range for an incident, the lower bound will be used to determine if the event qualifies as 15 or more. This question will be resolved based on the data reported in Wikipedia at 11:59 PM ET on the day after the close date. If the count crosses the highest answer bin threshold before the close date, the question will be closed retroactively with the crossing date as the end date of the question.

This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

description: The Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) Nigeria Security Tracker reports on countrywide violence stemming from political, economic and social grievances. Between 30 May 2019 and 1 November 2019, will United Kingdom or Republic of Ireland authorities attribute three or more deaths to Irish republican/nationalist or unionist/loyalist violence?
description: In April 2019, the New IRA admitted responsibility for a journalist's death in Londonderry/Derry (BBC, IrishTimes, Reuters). Some are concerned about a potential increase in Northern Ireland violence threatening the Good Friday agreement (CFR). Qualifying deaths can be simultaneous or isolated incidents. The attribution and deaths must all occur during the question's duration to qualify as 'yes.'

title: Before 30 July 2019, will Kosovo reduce or revoke the customs tariffs imposed in late 2018 on Serbian and Bosnian goods?
description: In November and December 2018, Kosovo implemented retaliatory customs tariffs against Serbia and Bosnia-Herzegovina (BBC, Reuters). After six months, the two countries declared they will retaliate against Kosovo if the tariff is not lifted before July 2019 (Intellinews, [in Serbian] SerbiaGov). The dispute casts more uncertainty around prospects of Kosovo's EU membership (PrishtinaInsight). Reducing or revoking the tariffs by exceptions for particular goods would not count. Temporary suspension, conditional or otherwise, of the tariffs would not count.
option_3: Yes, on both Serbian and Bosnian goods

title: Between 6 June 2019 and 30 June 2019, will anti-government protests in Albania result in a fatality?
description: Anti-government protests in Albania began in mid-February 2019 and have grown in intensity, including the use of firebombs against the office of Prime Minister Edi Rama, who is being accused of corruption and electoral crimes (EuroNews, BBC, RFERL).

title: Before 30 November 2019, will the European Council decide to open accession negotiations with Albania and/or North Macedonia?
description: Both Albania and North Macedonia are candidates for EU membership, and to begin membership negotiations with candidate countries the European Council decision must be unanimous (Europa1). In May 2019, the European Commission recommended opening accession negotiations with both Albania and North Macedonia, but there are still objections from several EU countries (Europa2, Politico, WSJ, Tsarizm, France24). A decision to open membership negotiations with the two countries could be made at the European Council's next scheduled meeting on 20-21 June 2019 (ECCalendar). The date accession negotiations would begin and any conditions included with a decision (e.g., Croatia in December 2004) are immaterial.
option_3: Yes, both Albania and North Macedonia

title: Will the UN Security Council adopt a resolution concerning Yemen between 9 June 2019 and 8 October 2019?
description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) adopts a resolution during the period of interest in which the country/region of interest appears in the short description in the Security Council Resolution table and/or is mentioned within the adopted resolution itself.

title: Before 30 November, will the UK's MI5 change their international terrorism threat level from SEVERE?
description: This question will be resolved based on MI5's reporting of the 'Current threat from international terrorism' heading found at https://www.mi5.gov.uk/threat-levels. The question will be resolved retroactively if the threat level changes prior to the close date.

title: What will be the average percentage cost of remitting $200 USD from Russia to Ukraine in Third Quarter 2019?

title: Between 18 July 2019 and 29 November 2019, will an asset declaration for Liberian President George Weah be made public?
description: In June 2019, Liberians held one of the largest anti-government protests since Liberia's last civil war (VOAnews). Amongst many demands, protesters want an open accounting of President Weah's assets (FrontPageAfricaOnline, LiberianObserver, France24).

title: Before 30 November 2019, will it be announced that the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) free trade agreement negotiations have concluded?
description: RCEP is a proposed trade agreement between Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) members and their free trade agreement partners (RCEP, ASEAN). Negotiators have worked on a trade deal for several years, and now hope to have an agreement by the end of the year (TheHinduBusinessLine, StraitsTimes). Ratification by the parties to the agreement is not required for a "yes" resolution.

title: Will a bill granting Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu immunity or protecting existing immunity from prosecution be put into law before 2 October 2019?
description: Any bill that is put into law that grants Benjamin Netanyahu immunity from prosecution or protects existing immunity from prosecution would count towards the resolution of this question. A new immunity law need not mention Benjamin Netanyahu by name to qualify for a "yes" resolution, in so long as his immunity from prosecution would be guaranteed and/or the ability for the Israel High Court of Justice to revoke his immunity under existing or future law be disallowed. Please seeÂ Washington Post and Jerusalem Post for additional information. A qualifying law will be considered to be put into law after being passed into law by the Knesset plenum and published in the Official Gazette (see: Legislative Process in the Knesset for more information).

title: Will any country/territory file a World Trade Organization dispute against China between 18 July 2019 and 29 November 2019?
What will be the unemployment rate for Italy in September 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using data from Eurostat. To access the relevant data: - Go to: Eurostat unemployment data; - The relevant row is 'Italy' and the relevant column is '2019M09.' This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: How many Total Registered Syrian Refugees will be reported by the UNHCR on 31 August 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using data from the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR). Outcome will be determined by the reported number of Total Registered Syrian Refugees as of noon ET on the date indicated according to the UNHCR's Syria Regional Refugee Response website.Â

title: Will the WHO declare a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC) between 18 July 2019 and 31 October 2019?
description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the World Health Organization (WHO) declares a PHEIC during the period of interest: WHO Statements.

title: Will the PITF Worldwide Atrocities Dataset record an event perpetrated by a non-state actor in India (IND) that starts between 18 July 2019 and 31 July 2019?
description: This question will resolve as "yes" if the Political Instability Task Force (PITF) Worldwide Atrocities Dataset records any event with a: - start date (Start Day, Start Month, Start Year) in the period of interest, inclusive, - 'Event Location: Country' is the country of interest, - 'Perpetrators: Perp State Role' is: -- 'Multiple Perpetrators (Non-State)'; -- 'Non-State, Internal, No State Sanction'; -- 'Transnational, Non-State'; or -- 'Unknown/Unclear/Other'. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

description:

title: What will be the daily closing price of gold on 30 October 2019 in USD?
description: This question will be resolved using the last daily London Bullion Market Association (LBMA) Gold Price USD (PM) http://www.lbma.org.uk/precious-metal-prices for the date of interest. To access the relevant data: - Select 'Table'; - Refer to the 'PM' column under 'USD.' Question will be closed on the day before the date of interest.

title: How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for Chile between 5 August 2019 and 15 September 2019 (epidemiological weeks 32-37, inclusive)?
description: FluNet is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. To access relevant data at http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12 make the following selections: - Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; - Filter by: Country of interest, - Year from: '2019', Week from: '1', - Year to: '2019' Week to: '53', - Click 'Display report.' This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the 'Total number of influenza positive viruses' (or .csv 'ALL_INF') column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the 16 October 2019 and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: Which option will prevail in the upcoming referendum on Bougainvillean independence in the Autonomous Region of Bougainville, Papua New Guinea?
description: An independence referendum will be held in Bougainville on 17 October 2019. The question being put to voters is:Â "Do you agree for Bougainville to have: (1) Greater Autonomy (2) Independence?"

description: In November 2018, U.S. President Donald Trump, Mexican President Enrique PeÃ±a Nieto, and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau signed the USMCA, a trade deal intended to replace the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) (NPR, USGov). The bill was introduced to Canada's Parliament in May 2019 (CTVNews, Process). Mexico ratified the USMCA on 19 June 2019 (Reuters).

title: Between 25 July 2019 and 29 November 2019, will Japan increase its consumption tax?
description: Japan's consumption tax is due to increase on 1 October 2019, but this has been delayed in the past (JapanMoF, JapanTimes1, JapanTimes2, Bloomberg). The consumption tax rate as of 24 July 2019 was 8% (Jetro).

title: Before 30 November 2019, will the temporary prohibition on direct passenger flights from Russia to Georgia be lifted?
description: Following protests in Georgia's capital of Tbilisi in June 2019, Russia imposed travel restrictions from Russia to Georgia (Kremlin, BBC, APNews, DW). Exceptions to the broader in-effect prohibition (e.g., emergency landings, heads of state travel allowances) will not count.

title: Between 25 July 2019 and 29 November 2019, will it be announced that Ansar Dine or Katiba Macina have met with or will meet with the Malian government for peace talks?
description: The planned date of a future meeting is immaterial to the question, provided that the initial announcement of the future meeting is made during the period of interest. For announcements made about a meeting that occurred in the past, both the announcement and the meeting must occur during the question's period of interest. Ethnic violence and jihadist insurgency have continued to increase in Mali since 2012, despite the Malian government's resignation in April 2019 (WashingtonPost, ReutersAfrica, UltimaRatio, CrisisGroup, VoANews, AlJazeera).

title: How many terrorist incidents with 15 or more dead (victims + perpetrators) will occur between 1 August 2019 and 31 August 2019 as reported by Wikipedia?
description: This question will be resolved using the number of terrorist incidents reported on Wikipedia's List of terrorist incidents page in which 15 or more deaths, both victims and perpetrators, are reported to have occurred during the period of interest. From the 'List of terrorist incidents' page, select 'List of terrorist incidents in August 2019.' If deaths are reported as a range for an incident, the lower bound will be used to determine if the event qualifies as 15 or more. Due to revisions to Wikipedia pages by numerous editors, the number of incidents may increase or decrease throughout the period of interest. This question will be resolved based on the data reported in Wikipedia at 11:59 PM ET on the day after the close date. If the count crosses the highest answer bin threshold before the close date, the question will be closed retroactively with the crossing date as the end date of the question.

title: How much crude oil will Algeria produce in July 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using oil production data measured in thousands of barrels per day (tb/d) reported for the country of interest for the month of interest in the "OPEC crude oil production based on secondary sources" table of the OPEC Monthly Oil Market Report http://www.opec.org/opec_web/en/publications/338.htm, expected to be published the first part of the following month. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.

title: What will be the daily closing price of France's CAC 40 (INDEXEURO: PX1) on 31 July 2019?
description: This question will be resolved using the daily closing price of the market of interest reported by Google Finance INDEXEURO:PX1. Question will be closed the day before the date of interest.

title: Will North Korea execute or be targeted in a national military attack between 25 July 2019 and 20 October 2019?
description: A "national military attack" includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country's national military forces (to include special forces) on 1) another country's military or military assets, anywhere, or 2) another country's territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A "cyber" attack will not qualify as a "national military attack."

title: Will the UN Security Council (UNSC) issue a press statement concerning violence in the UK between 1 August 2019 and 29 November 2019?
description: The UNSC press statement must explicitly reference the country of interest (or a location within the country) as a location of recent violence, including but not limited to terrorist attacks, military attacks, sectarian violence, violent civil unrest, or acts of government violence. The date on the statement will be used without any time zone conversion. This question will be resolved based on the press statements published on the UN website: UNSC press statements.

title: Will any country execute a national military attack within the Nagorno-Karabakh region between 1 August 2019 and 29 November 2019?
description: A "national military attack" within a specific geographic region involves one countryâs national military forces (to include special forces) employing conventional or unconventional weapons on 1) the military or military assets of another country, within the identified region, or 2) another country's territory, or citizens of another country, within the identified region â regardless of whether other regions are also targeted or impacted in the attack. A country executing a national military attack within its own territory (e.g., insurgency, domestic counter-terrorism) will not qualify for a "yes" resolution, unless otherwise specified within the question itself. A "cyber" attack will not qualify as a "national military attack."

title: Will the Aviation Safety Network record a hijacking or criminal occurrence between 1 November 2019 and 29 November 2019?
description: The Aviation Safety Network (ASN) covers accidents and safety issues regarding airliners, military transport planes and corporate jets. The ASN Safety Database contains detailed descriptions of over 20,300 incidents, hijackings and accidents. To access the relevant data: - Go to the ASN Safety Database; - Click on the year of interest. This question will resolve as "yes" if there is an incident with a 'H#' (Hijacking) or 'C#' (Criminal) under the 'cat' (category) column during the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the data source once each week sometime between 10:00 AM ET Wednesday and 4:00 PM ET Thursday, starting the Wednesday after the question close date and continuing once each week until the data are successfully retrieved.
